# Cursor Rules for RL Studio

## File Creation Rules

**CRITICAL: DO NOT CREATE .md FILES**
- Never create any .md files except README.md
- All documentation should be added to README.md only
- Do not create temporary .md files, guides, or documentation files
- Do not create COMMIT_MESSAGE.md, SETUP.md, GUIDE.md, or any other .md files
- If documentation is needed, update README.md instead

## Documentation Policy

- All project documentation belongs in README.md
- Do not split documentation into multiple .md files
- Keep README.md comprehensive and up-to-date
- Never create separate documentation files

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript for frontend code
- Use Python for backend code
- Follow existing code patterns
- Keep components focused and modular

## File Naming

- Use kebab-case for file names
- Do not create files with generic names like "guide.md", "setup.md", "notes.md"
- All documentation goes in README.md only

